data.title: Ditto "Weird Place" review.
data.text: Whoever thinks this is a "Country Bar" has never been south of Hinkley.  Hip hop and rock DJ music, drunk 20 somethings standing around blocking off what little dance floor there is, and there were drinks spilled all over the floor too.

data.title: Charming Country Bar
data.text: We have been to Spurs a few times.  I think the staff usually out number the patrons, but they are super friendly !!  The drinks are strong and the dancing was long ...

data.title: I want to love it...
data.text:
They did a great job decorating this place, and when they get a good band that draws a crowd it's a fun bar to be in. However:

They shot themselves in the foot by always charging a cover when their other bar, Aces, which is next door, is free to get in. It set a bad precedent and after people realized it often wasn't worth it (always less crowded than next door) they stopped being willing to pay to get inside. Also, not everyone likes country, or is willing to pay a premium to listen to it.

So, they started branching out with karoke and having rock bands come, which I think disheartened avid country fans. I know Spurs co-sponsors street dances in the summer which draw a huge crowd. I just think they fell short somewhere of making this venue really fun. I still like the space and the idea, but it's tough to make it a destination for a night out when the party always seems to be somewhere else.

data.title: I don't really get it
data.text: Weird place...seems to be struggling with an identity crisis.  We expected a country bar, yet the music playing inside was hip-hop/dance.  The server didn't know what alcohol they served so ordering was a bit of a struggle.  The selection was minimal and the bartenders came across as irritated and annoyed. Just a strange experience.
